Still great.  She sells World's Best Cat Litter (made with corn; I wasn't impressed with it when I tried it a few years ago), and Close to Nature (made with soybeans), which she recommends over WBCL.    Why not the standard clay litter?  It's got a very fine dust that gets into the cat's lungs and yours, and it contains aluminum, which isn't good for anyone's brain.  Also, corn and soybeans are biodegradable industrial waste products.  However, they're probably pesticide-loaded.  Can't win!  I'm looking for something that clumps and controls odors decently, though.  I love talking to the owner.  She's super-nice and super-knowledgeable.

